properties.Name: CustomerAssignmentProceeding
properties.Description:
An assignment for the creditors benefit, which is similar to a Composition plan, but is more formal.

Title to the debtor's property is assigned to a trustee that will sell the property for the benefit of the creditor.

In an Assignment, property in the hands of the Trustee cannot be attached by other creditors.

Columns.Name: AssignmentProceedingId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of an Assignment Proceeding.

Columns.Name: AssignmentEffectiveDate
Columns.Description: The effective date of the Assignment Proceeding.

Columns.Name: OutstandingAmount
Columns.Description: The outstanding or existing debt amount.

Columns.Name: AssignmentProceedingAgreementStatement
Columns.Description: The statement detailing the assignment proceeding.

Columns.Name: CustomerId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Customer.
